//Element 0
Welcome to the Chemistry Lab VR. Your first experiment is to determine metallic ions of chloride salts using a flame test. On the lab bench you can see five beakers each containing a different metal chloride solution. #line:01


//Element 1
The first solution is Potassium Chloride. #line:04

//Element 2
The second solution is Lithium Chloride. #line:05

//Element 3
The third solution is Calcium Chloride. #line:06

//Element 4
The fourth solution is Copper Chloride. #line:07

//Element 5
And the fifth solution is Sodium Chloride. #line:08


//Element 6
Hold up each beaker to inspect the color of the salt solution. As you can see only the copper chloride solution has a light blue color. The rest are clear. Once you're done click Next to continue. #line:09

