//Element 7
To execute the flame test, you will need to use the Bunsen burner to your left.  #line:11

//Element 8
For this experiment, the bunsen burner has been lit up for you. #line:12 

//Element 9
Notice the color of the flame.<br><br>The flame has a bluish color and burns with a roaring sound.This is a luminous flame and is produced when the airhole is open. #line:13

//Element 10
Most of the chemistry experiments you will do in the lab will require this type of flame.<br><br>Once you're comfortable, press the Next button to continue to the next part of the experiment. #line:14

